The National Emergency Agency of Nigeria has advised 11 local government areas of Rivers State to prepare for flood by identifying the designated internally displaced persons’ camps in the state. The  south-south zonal coordinator  of NEMA, Walson Brandin, yesterday in Port Harcourt identified the affected local government areas as Abia/Odua, Oyigbo, Okrika, Ahoada east, Ahoada west, Ogu/bolo, Akuku-toru, Asari-toru, Bonny, Port Harcourt City and Opopo-Nkoro. He said that the call became necessary following recent forecast by the Nigerian Metrological Agency that 11 local government areas of the state would suffer severe flooding. He said the flood expected this year would be more serious than that of last year.  Red alert as floods come rumbling again page 36 Harvest: Flood heightens tension in Rivers Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin